+# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260325-204116-f888
+
+## Findings
+1. [P1] Fix 1 — Guest name save silently no-ops when no current guest ID — In [pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3142) the save handler exits on `if (!currentGuest?.id || !guestNameInput.trim()) return;`, so the ✓ button wired at [pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L458) becomes a no-op whenever the guest has not been restored/created yet. That matches the reported UX: no toast, no state transition back to read-only, and no feedback despite the button being enabled. FIX: change `handleUpdateGuestName` so it only guards on empty input, conditionally calls `base44.entities.SessionGuest.update()` when `currentGuest?.id` exists, and in all cases saves the trimmed name locally, updates visible state, shows `toast.success(...)`, and exits edit mode instead of returning silently.
+2. [P1] Fix 1 — Guest name has no persistence or restore path — The page initializes `guestNameInput` as `useState('')` at [pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1356), but there is no `menuapp_guest_name` read/write anywhere in the file. The current save path only updates Base44 when `currentGuest.id` exists and then clears the input at [pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3154), so a refresh loses the name whenever the backend guest record is missing or has not been restored yet. FIX: write the trimmed name to `localStorage.setItem('menuapp_guest_name', ...)` during save, read it on page load to prefill guest-name state, and hydrate the non-editing display from that stored value when no persisted guest name is available from `currentGuest`.
+3. [P2] Fix 2 — Post-submit cart state leaves the drawer without a next action — The submitted-orders block ends at [pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L777), and the next section is gated by `cart.length > 0` at [pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L780). When the order is sent and the cart is cleared, Section 2 disappears and nothing replaces it, so the user is left with a dead-end white area below "Ваши заказы". FIX: insert a dedicated CTA block between Section 3 and Section 2 that renders only for `cart.length === 0 && myOrders.length > 0`, uses `tr('cart.add_more', 'Добавить к заказу')`, spans full width with a 44px+ tap target, and calls the existing `onClose` prop to return the user to the menu.
+4. [P2] Fix 3 — Order rating control is rendered in the compact size with no added hit area — In the cart orders section, the only rating control is still `<Rating ... size="sm" />` at [pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L723), inside a plain flex row with no extra touch padding at [pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx#L722). On a 375px mobile target, this keeps the order-rating affordance in its smallest variant exactly where accurate tapping matters most. FIX: increase the cart-order rating control to the next supported size (`md` if available) or wrap it in additional vertical padding such as `py-2` so each star meets the required mobile touch target without changing MenuView ratings.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 4 findings (0 P0, 2 P1, 2 P2, 0 P3)
+
+## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
+- Overall clarity: 3
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 1 — the expected restore behavior says to pre-fill `guestNameInput` from `localStorage`, but the non-editing UI displays `currentGuest.name` / `guestDisplay`; it is not explicit whether the saved local name must also appear immediately in read-only mode when no backend guest exists yet.
+- Missing context (what info would have helped): The task references `BUGS_MASTER.md` in the batch header, but the speed rules also say not to read outside the page folder. A clear statement on whether root-level references are intentionally out of scope would remove that conflict.
+- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): Whether the requested review should also produce the repo-level `review_*.md` / `commands_*.log` artifacts from `AGENTS.md`, since the user-facing task only names the pipeline findings file.

